activities.text: Grade: 4.0

The Manufacturing Leadership certificate provides a unique but essential foundation for understanding and optimizing a manufacturing organization. While many courses in manufacturing focus on the mechanical operations and processes, this certificate focuses on maximizing the performance of the entire system. Achieving the highest levels of performance starts with design of products and systems, integrating the contributions of a complex network of suppliers, and coordinating production according to key constraints throughout the supply chain. Finally, the most effective route to achieving continuous improvement in this environment is the integrated application of Lean, Six Sigma, and Theory of Constraints.

fixedListComponent.text: Cylix has been a partner for years on the owner side of the project and has proven time and again to be incredibly valuable.  Cylix is one of the most detail oriented people I've worked with but at the same time an outgoing personality, two traits that are seldom found together. section_components.caption: February 10, 2021, Cylix worked with Darren on the same team
section_components.subtitle: Heroic Performance Coach @ Heroic | Coaching, Mental Performance, Workshop Facilitator, Personal Trainer, CoreFitinc

fixedListComponent.text: Darren has one of the strongest positive, motivational personalities I have ever encountered. Darren is a champion of strong morals and ethics, combined with customer service. As such, he was always promoting our team of managers to do the right thing. He led our group through some difficult decisions and always put the patients and employee safety first. We saw situations where caregivers were being injured during patient lifting scenarios. Darren supported equipment repairs, tracking/metrics, and the injury prevention program. Darren could be seen fostering connections throughout the day with patients and caregivers on a personal level and he genuinely cares for those around him.  He has strong core values and leadership skills that are exemplary. I highly recommend Darren, he is a highly motivated, action-oriented, results driven leader.

fixedListComponent.text: Brian has been one of the most influential project managers I have gotten to work with. He has exemplary leadership skills and is able to forecast both the owners needs and all of the trade partners needs in parallel. Brian worked with us on several large initiatives including a large Teaching-Health Clinic and a ground-up 100 bed inpatient behavioral health hospital. Brian brings multiple skills to the table and is able to manage complex multiphase projects with various contracting styles (IPD, GMP, Lump Sum, Lean IPD, Design/Build ). Brian also effectively managed and maintained the project budget, he communicated all potential issues to the team and kept everyone actively engaged in creative problem solving. If our healthcare system ever looked to build any large design build campus I would request we engage Brian and his team as their skill set has proven to be second to none.

linkedin_data.headline: Hospital CFO | Revenue Cycle Management | Strategic Analysis | Physician Practice Management | Lean Process Improvement | Financial Turnaround Specialist | Medicare LOS Reductions | Mentorship
linkedin_data.summary:
Offering disciplined and principled leadership that drives margins, while elevating quality outcomes and patient experience.

Visionary Financial Executive – accomplished Chief Financial Officer with expertise in acute care hospitals within national health systems. Skilled in directing financial teams through both full-time and interim assignments in environments ranging from completely independent hospitals to highly centralized and matrixed leadership structures.

Financial Turnaround Specialist - expertise in delivering financial turnarounds in non-profit and for-profits through improvements in labor and revenue cycle management, as well as debt restructuring and Medicare LOS reductions. 

Strategic Partner, Mentor - recognized for effective organizational collaboration and mentorship of high-potential finance staff who have advanced to senior and C-suite roles.

Stewardship and finance run deep in my DNA, which makes my work a life-long passion.  My parents claim that my first complete sentence as a toddler was "How much does that cost?"

linkedin_data.top_skills_by_endorsements: Strategic Planning, Executive Management, Investments, Business Strategy, Cash Flow

description.text: Chosen for financial leadership of a 160-bed, $250M net revenue acute-care hospital.  Matrix oversight of Southern Oregon Service Area physician practices, homecare, and hospice to grow value-based services in a geographically independent integrated delivery system.  Lead ministry financial improvement and partnered with regional peers to similarly succeed.
Served as interim CFO for two acute care hospitals, completing a bond financing, renegotiating managed care contracts, restarting the revenue cycle, and focusing on a growth path to sustainability.

Selected to transition a standalone a $240M net revenue, 190-bed hospital to adopt system processes, structure, and philosophy while converting multiple clinical and financial systems.  Managed 110 direct and matrix reports in finance, revenue cycle, and supply chain.

Selected to restore financial leadership and reporting function to 43-bed rural community hospital that had been without a CFO for seven months, as it transitioned from a county authority.  Preserved 120+ jobs by preventing hospital closure. Analyzed turnaround scenarios and recommended leasing the facility. Positioned facility for growth and system integration.

Directed all financial activities of 139-bed, acute care hospital with $140M in annual net revenue and a highly seasonal census fluctuation of nearly 40%. Reintroduced DRG clinical documentation program, enhancing case mix by $1.6M while improving mortality / severity ratios by 76%. Negotiated hospital physician subsidy reductions of $1.1M in and $220K in anesthesia. Partnered with employed physician practices to reduce subsidy from $7M to $3.8M.
FHZ Turnaround in Tampa Bay Business Journal

section_components.caption: March 4, 2016, Hal managed Paul directly
section_components.subtitle: Retired

fixedListComponent.text: Paul has one of the sharpest financial minds of anyone with whom I have worked.  The turnaround and reconciliation work he performed in a hospital that had no financial reporting or accounting performed for over six months, was incredible.  He efficiently and professionally handled an extremely difficult financial challenge.  His work ethic is second to none.  Paul is an individual of high ethical integrity and morals.  His background includes functioning as a CFO of individual hospitals and working at the corporate level.  This broad experience gives Paul the ability to perform analytics from the needs of the smallest facility as well as from a regional and corporate perspective. I highly recommend Paul and would be happy to discuss in more detail his performance while working with me.  I can be reached at hcoble@gmail.com or on my cell at 770-367-6840.  Hal Coble

section_components.caption: July 1, 2020, Paul worked with Tricia but on different teams
section_components.subtitle: UChicago Medicine | AdventHealth

fixedListComponent.text: Tricia was a key part of our hospital IT team that consistently delivered top-quartile performance in our 40+ hospital system, and set the bar high for our region.  Tricia took an innovative approach to troubleshooting the device, network, and application issues, and was exceptional in her consistent solutions, follow through, and seeing our projects to completion.  Regardless of whether she was working with the C-Suite or a small off-campus location, she was persistent in seeking a solution.  Towards the end of my time working with Tricia and her team, we had a surprise thank-you party for the team to notice and appreciate their contribution to our success, and turnout from our leadership and staff further demonstrated what Tricia's importance was to our operational and technical goals.  I'm very pleased to recommend Tricia as a positive for any IT team!

activities.text: Grade: 4.0

The Manufacturing Leadership certificate provides a unique but essential foundation for understanding and optimizing a manufacturing organization. While many courses in manufacturing focus on the mechanical operations and processes, this certificate focuses on maximizing the performance of the entire system. Achieving the highest levels of performance starts with design of products and systems, integrating the contributions of a complex network of suppliers, and coordinating production according to key constraints throughout the supply chain. Finally, the most effective route to achieving continuous improvement in this environment is the integrated application of Lean, Six Sigma, and Theory of Constraints.

section_components.caption: January 15, 2021, Cylix was Brian’s client
section_components.subtitle: Construction Estimator at MACC Estimating

fixedListComponent.text: Cylix has been a partner for years on the owner side of the project and has proven time and again to be incredibly valuable.  Cylix is one of the most detail oriented people I've worked with but at the same time an outgoing personality, two traits that are seldom found together.  He does his research on the topic at hand and comes to the table well educated and ready to offer solutions to whatever issue may arise.  He has an extensive background in acute care hospital construction and understands clinical needs that impact design and construction.  Cylix is dedicated to the best outcome for all parties and is great to work with, a high performer in all environments.

section_components.caption: February 10, 2021, Cylix worked with Darren on the same team
section_components.subtitle: Heroic Performance Coach @ Heroic | Coaching, Mental Performance, Workshop Facilitator, Personal Trainer, CoreFitinc

fixedListComponent.text: Darren has one of the strongest positive, motivational personalities I have ever encountered. Darren is a champion of strong morals and ethics, combined with customer service. As such, he was always promoting our team of managers to do the right thing. He led our group through some difficult decisions and always put the patients and employee safety first. We saw situations where caregivers were being injured during patient lifting scenarios. Darren supported equipment repairs, tracking/metrics, and the injury prevention program. Darren could be seen fostering connections throughout the day with patients and caregivers on a personal level and he genuinely cares for those around him.  He has strong core values and leadership skills that are exemplary. I highly recommend Darren, he is a highly motivated, action-oriented, results driven leader.

section_components.caption: January 29, 2021, Cylix worked with Brian but they were at different companies
section_components.subtitle: Construction Estimator at MACC Estimating

fixedListComponent.text: Brian has been one of the most influential project managers I have gotten to work with. He has exemplary leadership skills and is able to forecast both the owners needs and all of the trade partners needs in parallel. Brian worked with us on several large initiatives including a large Teaching-Health Clinic and a ground-up 100 bed inpatient behavioral health hospital. Brian brings multiple skills to the table and is able to manage complex multiphase projects with various contracting styles (IPD, GMP, Lump Sum, Lean IPD, Design/Build ). Brian also effectively managed and maintained the project budget, he communicated all potential issues to the team and kept everyone actively engaged in creative problem solving. If our healthcare system ever looked to build any large design build campus I would request we engage Brian and his team as their skill set has proven to be second to none.

linkedin_data.headline: Hospital CFO | Revenue Cycle Management | Strategic Analysis | Physician Practice Management | Lean Process Improvement | Financial Turnaround Specialist | Medicare LOS Reductions | Mentorship
linkedin_data.summary:
Offering disciplined and principled leadership that drives margins, while elevating quality outcomes and patient experience.

Visionary Financial Executive – accomplished Chief Financial Officer with expertise in acute care hospitals within national health systems. Skilled in directing financial teams through both full-time and interim assignments in environments ranging from completely independent hospitals to highly centralized and matrixed leadership structures.

Financial Turnaround Specialist - expertise in delivering financial turnarounds in non-profit and for-profits through improvements in labor and revenue cycle management, as well as debt restructuring and Medicare LOS reductions. 

Strategic Partner, Mentor - recognized for effective organizational collaboration and mentorship of high-potential finance staff who have advanced to senior and C-suite roles.

Stewardship and finance run deep in my DNA, which makes my work a life-long passion.  My parents claim that my first complete sentence as a toddler was "How much does that cost?"

description.text: Chosen for financial leadership of a 160-bed, $250M net revenue acute-care hospital.  Matrix oversight of Southern Oregon Service Area physician practices, homecare, and hospice to grow value-based services in a geographically independent integrated delivery system.  Lead ministry financial improvement and partnered with regional peers to similarly succeed.
Served as interim CFO for two acute care hospitals, completing a bond financing, renegotiating managed care contracts, restarting the revenue cycle, and focusing on a growth path to sustainability.

Selected to transition a standalone a $240M net revenue, 190-bed hospital to adopt system processes, structure, and philosophy while converting multiple clinical and financial systems.  Managed 110 direct and matrix reports in finance, revenue cycle, and supply chain.

Selected to restore financial leadership and reporting function to 43-bed rural community hospital that had been without a CFO for seven months, as it transitioned from a county authority.  Preserved 120+ jobs by preventing hospital closure. Analyzed turnaround scenarios and recommended leasing the facility. Positioned facility for growth and system integration.

Directed all financial activities of 139-bed, acute care hospital with $140M in annual net revenue and a highly seasonal census fluctuation of nearly 40%. Reintroduced DRG clinical documentation program, enhancing case mix by $1.6M while improving mortality / severity ratios by 76%. Negotiated hospital physician subsidy reductions of $1.1M in and $220K in anesthesia. Partnered with employed physician practices to reduce subsidy from $7M to $3.8M.
FHZ Turnaround in Tampa Bay Business Journal

education.degree: Master of Business Administration (M.B.A.), Healthcare Administration

fixedListComponent.text: His keen intellect, diverse experience and knowledge base within a hospital, along with his ability to work with team members from all disciplines and 'get things done' have been an asset to our organization. section_components.caption: March 4, 2016, Hal managed Paul directly
section_components.subtitle: Retired

fixedListComponent.text: Paul has one of the sharpest financial minds of anyone with whom I have worked.  The turnaround and reconciliation work he performed in a hospital that had no financial reporting or accounting performed for over six months, was incredible.  He efficiently and professionally handled an extremely difficult financial challenge.  His work ethic is second to none.  Paul is an individual of high ethical integrity and morals.  His background includes functioning as a CFO of individual hospitals and working at the corporate level.  This broad experience gives Paul the ability to perform analytics from the needs of the smallest facility as well as from a regional and corporate perspective. I highly recommend Paul and would be happy to discuss in more detail his performance while working with me.  I can be reached at hcoble@gmail.com or on my cell at 770-367-6840.  Hal Coble

section_components.caption: July 1, 2020, Paul worked with Tricia but on different teams
section_components.subtitle: UChicago Medicine | AdventHealth

fixedListComponent.text: Tricia was a key part of our hospital IT team that consistently delivered top-quartile performance in our 40+ hospital system, and set the bar high for our region.  Tricia took an innovative approach to troubleshooting the device, network, and application issues, and was exceptional in her consistent solutions, follow through, and seeing our projects to completion.  Regardless of whether she was working with the C-Suite or a small off-campus location, she was persistent in seeking a solution.  Towards the end of my time working with Tricia and her team, we had a surprise thank-you party for the team to notice and appreciate their contribution to our success, and turnout from our leadership and staff further demonstrated what Tricia's importance was to our operational and technical goals.  I'm very pleased to recommend Tricia as a positive for any IT team!

linkedin_data.headline: People First, Last, and Everywhere in Between
linkedin_data.summary:
The things we do - jobs, hobbies, whatever - are made only by the people we get to share them with. I have had the good fortune to experience many great relationships. I want to dedicate my life to working directly with and for people. My goal is to spread as widely as possible the basis for my great relationships, namely humor, self-awareness, and trust.

I believe everything in life can be improved, that there is no maximum to what can be accomplished. There are always skills to acquire, facts to learn, and character traits to further develop. I take great pride in my commitment to pushing myself beyond my previous limits. This constant pushing has led to trust and praise everywhere I have been. I easily win the respect of my peers and supervisors through my unyielding work ethic, independence, and calm, reliable nature.

CliftonStrengths: Adaptability, Empathy, Restorative, Intellection, Connectedness

description.text:
Projects were mostly centered around growth and expansion so included the infrastructure build for new departments and clinics as well as acquisitions.  Traditional Project Manager responsibilities like keeping projects on schedule, within scope and budget all while maintaining clear and concise communications with team members and stakeholders were key to success.  Additional projects have also included managing application teams for Epic department builds and changes.

Acquisitions
-Several small Primary Care Practices (WA and CA)
-Radiant Care (Western WA)
-Medford Medical Clinic (Medford, OR)
-South Sound Surgery Center (Olympia, WA)
-South Sound Pulmonary Associates (Olympia, WA)
-Oregon Neurology (Portland, OR Area)

Additional Contributions
-High Reliability Champion
-Community Connect Technical Review Team Member
-PMO Subject Matter Expert
-Led bi-weekly "brown bag" team meeting

Initial position began as a team member to help Providence St. Peter's Hospital in Olympia Washington with the deployment of the Epic EMR. After a few months was tasked with the responsibility of leading the team and reporting the status of the implementation of equipment to local, regional, and system wide leadership. As this was the first of many deployments of Epic for Providence status reports and other tracking tools were not available and needed created. Once Epic was fully deployed and had gone live at the hospital work transitioned to managing other projects that included equipping and preparing several new clinics and departments with technology and the Epic EMR. Eventually the experience gained was deemed valuable and was requested to travel and train other Providence desktop teams for deployments of Epic in Walla Walla and Spokane. This type of work led to the Project Coordinator role at Providence as a full time employee.

Standard Desktop Technician responsibilities and tasks
-Troubleshooting of printers and workstations
-Installation of software
-DHCP reservations
-Asset management
-Customer service

Epic Lead responsibilities and tasks
-Assign daily work to team
-Keep teams on track to meet deadlines
-Verify configurations
-Lead print mapping for Epic
-Train staff & create documentation
-Create tracking and reporting documents and tools
-Report status to Key Stakeholders

section_components.caption: July 28, 2022, William (Al) was Mike’s client
section_components.subtitle: Executive Account Manager - Enterprise West @ CDW Healthcare

fixedListComponent.text: After working with Al for years now, it’s easy to see his attention to detail, creative thinking in a pinch, and exceptional organizational skills have helped him complete countless projects efficiently time and time again. Keep up the great work, Al!

section_components.caption: February 25, 2014, Theron was senior to William (Al) but didn't manage William (Al) directly
section_components.subtitle: Driving performance at the nexus of technology and business leadership

fixedListComponent.text:
I have had the pleasure to work with Al in his role as a Project Coordinator for Providence Health and Services.  Al worked on end-user experience, coordinating hardware and software implementation and configuration, providing go-live support, and acting as a critical communication leader throughout the initiative.

Al's focus on providing outstanding customer service and satisfaction, combined with his ability to juggle multiple demands made a dramatic difference in our Epic deployment.

Al is an honest "straight shooter" and would be an asset in any team.

section_components.caption: April 15, 2024, William (Al) was senior to Johnny but didn't manage Johnny directly
section_components.subtitle: Senior Leader Orchestrating Strategic Programs & Projects | Business Operations Expert | Change Management Champion | Driving Digital Transformation | Activating Strategies with Data Analytics & Lean Six Sigma

fixedListComponent.text: Working with Johnny during our Epic implementation was a pleasure. His professionalism and leadership skills shined bright and when we needed individuals to step up to lead groups for testing end user devices, Johnny stepped up to the challenge. While balancing the regular tasks requested of his team to support caregivers during the implementation which included training, fielding questions, and keeping caregivers that were new to the software organized and on track to be prepared for the Go-Live Johnny also assisted my team. There were several tasks we requested of him and his team which included validation of hardware deployment and configuration and testing of all workstations. During the main event for testing Johnny and his team Johnny and his team did a great job working around patient care and caregivers as this was a production environment in an active hospital. His demeanor with peers and colleagues was exemplary and if we had an opening on our team, I am confident we would have gladly recruited him to work for us. His clinical experience and understanding of technology is very helpful when bridging the gap for customers.

section_components.caption: August 17, 2022, William (Al) was senior to Alvin but didn't manage Alvin directly
section_components.subtitle: Principal Project Program Manager at UnitedHealth

fixedListComponent.text:
Over the past two year plus I have had the pleasure of working directly with Alvin Chung at Providence Health & Services. During the time we worked together my role was a Principal Project Manager and later a Senior Manager of a team that was heavily involved with the implementation of the Epic electronic medical record for Covenant Health in Texas and New Mexico. My direct reports interacted with Alvin daily and I served as an escalation point for the holistic project.

Alvin is professional, accountable, and possesses a passion for the details and customer satisfaction. In his role as an IS Project Manager he was responsible to attend and report out progress and barriers daily, communicate directly with the clinical caregivers when scheduling and entering their workspace. The clinical environment takes compassion and empathy; both of which Alvin displays. 

Other key skills would be his ability to develop relationships and trust with the key stakeholders and team members. This was accomplished by being accountable, knowledgeable, flexible, and approachable. Any organization would be lucky to have him.

description.text:
Worked on the leadership team that deployed the Epic EMR to 15 hospitals and over 300 clinics.  The projects consisted of standard project life-cycle milestones including scoping, budgeting, monitoring, and reporting.  The project was large and complex, especially during a pandemic, but ultimately was successful.  By the third wave the error rate for workstations and printers was less than 4%.  Directly led the Deployment Support Specialist Team which each had a facility they were responsible for.

Orange County / High Desert (5 Hospitals - May 2021)
•	End User Devices Deployed ~14K
•	Workstations and Printers Tested ~20K
Northern California (5 Hospitals - September 2021)
•	End User Devices Deployed ~12K
•	Workstations and Printers Tested ~15K
Texas / New Mexico & Grace Surgical Hospital (5 Hospitals - March 2022)
•	End User Devices Deployed ~9K
•	Workstations and Printers Tested ~15K

Led several large-scale projects for Epic implementations
- Worked on data conversion due to custodian of records requirements
- Transitions of network and telecom services to the new organization
- Facilitate design meetings for call trees and phone/fax number assignments
- Design future state floor plans demonstrating where new equipment would be installed
- Lead the Technical Dress Rehearsal
- Go-Live support

Projects were mostly centered around growth and expansion so included the infrastructure build for new departments and clinics as well as acquisitions.  Traditional Project Manager responsibilities like keeping projects on schedule, within scope and budget all while maintaining clear and concise communications with team members and stakeholders were key to success.  Additional projects have also included managing application teams for Epic department builds and changes.

Acquisitions
-Several small Primary Care Practices (WA and CA)
-Radiant Care (Western WA)
-Medford Medical Clinic (Medford, OR)
-South Sound Surgery Center (Olympia, WA)
-South Sound Pulmonary Associates (Olympia, WA)
-Oregon Neurology (Portland, OR Area)

Additional Contributions
-High Reliability Champion
-Community Connect Technical Review Team Member
-PMO Subject Matter Expert
-Led bi-weekly "brown bag" team meeting

As a Project Coordinator responsibilities included keeping deployments of equipment and configurations on track leading up to the Technical Dress Rehearsal while managing the creation of workstation and printer records for Epic. The Dress Rehearsal took planning with the local staff as well as analysts of all the applications utilized in Epic at the site and then execution and communication of results to Executive and local leadership.

Eventually the experience gained was deemed valuable and was requested to travel and train other Providence desktop teams for deployments of Epic in Walla Walla and Spokane. This type of work led to the Project Coordinator role at Providence as a full time employee.

linkedin_data.name: Kit Thomson (Worley)
linkedin_data.headline: Divisional Compliance and Technology Director of Pharmacy at Providence Health & Services
linkedin_data.summary:
MISSION

To align my skills and talents with what is needed in the healthcare system to build effective and efficient systems that support optimized patient-centric results. 

WHAT HAS HELPED ME SUCCEED

Proven track record of high performance; employing strong organizational skills, leadership, efficiency, and thorough knowledge regarding many aspects of pharmacy processes and regulations to achieve organization goals: cost-savings, quality, labor efficiency, timely delivery, and safety.

WHERE I'VE MADE A DIFFERENCE

Improving the medication use process and unifying teams to drive organizational change are achievements throughout my career. 

A few select examples include:
● Exceeded formulation management and utilization savings goal each year.  Saved $441K in formulary management against a goal of $100K, and captured $3M in 340B savings.. 
● Oversight of design and remodel of a hospital central pharmacy, including longitudinal LEAN project focused on optimizing workflow efficiency and reducing waste. 
● Controlled Substance accountability operation and strategic planning for 8 hospitals that included design of medication use system and development of regulatory mock audit procedures.  

MY LEADERSHIP STYLE

I bring a collaborative leadership style that is focused and productive. I take pride in the assisting caregivers to utilize their skills and talents in ways that are meaningful to them and the organization.  A hospital CEO once said to me, "I appreciate that I never have to worry about pharmacy because I know you have it all handled."  

WHAT SETS ME APART

● Dedication
● Organization
● Integrity
● Compassion
● Work-ethic
● Technology expertise
● Transparency

description.text: Serving as IS Program Manager in the Mergers, Acquistions & Technology Enablement group working on multiple new Construction & Remodel Projects and Programs from small Clinic Acquisitions to large Hospital buildouts.  Projects encompassed the deployment of new Networking, Telecom and Desktop Equipment as well as migration from Paper or legacy EMR systems to EPIC in extremely constrained schedules.

Served as Program Manager for the Careconnect Command Center, Triage Desk & Call Center Projects, overseeing the implementation of a 300+ user, 150+ VoIP ACD Phone System to support the CareConnect Go-Live, the largest single-day, full-functionality Go-Live in Epic's history.

Managed the transition of end device systems infrastructure into the new Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Center & Santa Monica UCLA Orthopaedic Hospital, ensuring smooth IT decommissioning of the Center of Health Sciences (CHS) Building.

Led and prioritized the workload of 3 teams consisting of 12 project technicians and 3 team leads, ensuring successful completion of enterprise-wide projects including Y2K, Desktop Optimization, and Token Ring to Ethernet Conversion.

Conducted technical due diligence activities, assessing appropriate technologies, solution designs, and vendor selections.

Oversaw the hiring, training, and disbandment of the Ethernet Project team.

Provided comprehensive desktop, server, and network support to employees, ensuring compliance with company policies and procedures.

Designed and implemented a Microsoft Access Invoicing and Sales application for the company's Product Sales Division.

description.text: As a Clinical Informatics Specialist, I served as an Epic liaison to the clinical staff. Helping to identify, troubleshoot, research and present issues with Epic to Analyst’s for resolution. I have become well versed with Most Epic applications, such as ASAP, IP Nurse, Ambulatory, Ancillary services, OP Hospital based applications (a blend of OP and IP), and Op-Time. Due to working within such a small group, with no local analyst’s [unlike other similar positions to which the same work profile offered a large enough team to focus their energy on one or two applications], it was important for me to become familiar with all of these applications.

As a US Soldier it is my duty to serve and protect my country. As a Soldier Medic I get an opportunity to do this through Medicine. The combat medic course has trained me well beyond what you would expect from the equivalent schooling in the civilian sector. I have been trained to Provide Emergency medical care, Limited primary care, In-Patient basic care procedures, including documentation, supportive care, casualty triage/ processing, minor acute care, force health protection, as well as Evacuation in a variety of operational and clinical settings, from point of injury and or illness, through the continuum of care. This training has given me the knowledge base on which I have built my career!

description.text:
Founded in 1856, Providence Health & Services is the third largest health system in the United States. Identity and Access Management is the central hub for all 82,000+ caregivers (employees) computer access to Providence Systems. All new hires, after passing their background checks, come through the IAM department to receive credentials to do their jobs. We provision all the access they need to perform their work effectively. Some of my roles include:

Identity Management
   ◊ Manage identities using SailPoint
   ◊ Manual identity correlation where multiple users have similar identity characteristics.
   ◊ Whiteglove identity creations and modifications where automation is not applicable.
   ◊ Whiteglove terminations where automation is not applicable.
   ◊ Extensive use of Active Directory/Group Policy in a multi-forest domain structure

Direct Customer Interaction
   ◊ Superior Customer Service
   ◊ Tier 2 support for end user issues

Epic Provisioning/Deprovisioning, Unix for advanced Epic access builds
   ◊ Building, updating, and terminating Epic records for users (EMP, SER)
   ◊ Building and terminating Unix accounts
   ◊ Heavy use of scripting for automating tasks and bulk-loading new user builds

Application Access
   ◊ Grant access to over 4,000 applications through group membership
   ◊ Manual application account builds for legacy applications such as Cerner, PACS, Unix, etc.

description.text:
Gained knowledge in developing and starting a non-profit organization. I have had experience in writing bylaws, articles of incorporation, and researching non-profit laws and regulations. Beyond the paperwork and legal aspects, have gained an immense amount of knowledge in project management, fundraising events, and shipping.

I served as the project coordinator for our first large shipment to Tanzania, where I gained valuable experience in communicating with our partners overseas, as well as coordinating with multiple parties to ensure a seamless process in shipping and collecting the donated goods. I also served on the event planning committee. Our success in reaching out to local companies and hosting fundraising events allowed us to raise the funds necessary to send our first package to Tanzania.

https://twitter.com/#!/sharecycle
http://www.facebook.com/sharecycle

As a Health Promotion Coordinator I developed health education materials which were used in conducting onsite wellness workshops. These interactive wellness workshops consisted of approximately 10-20 participants and allowed individuals to be directly involved in their wellness goals through awareness and health education. 

Assisted in the development of processes and procedures which were required for NCQM accreditation for wellness programs. This consisted of structured and detailed documentation of the implementation and administration of our wellness. 

Developed a proposal for implementing a wellness initiative within the Native American community in San Diego, focusing on culture, beliefs, and values. Conducted research and used best practices to develop a culturally appropriate program, providing community members an opportunity to improve their health while remaining sensitive to their culture and beliefs.

section_components.caption: April 15, 2024, William (Al) was senior to Johnny but didn't manage Johnny directly
section_components.subtitle: Senior Leader Orchestrating Strategic Programs & Projects | Business Operations Expert | Change Management Champion | Driving Digital Transformation | Activating Strategies with Data Analytics & Lean Six Sigma

fixedListComponent.text: Working with Johnny during our Epic implementation was a pleasure. His professionalism and leadership skills shined bright and when we needed individuals to step up to lead groups for testing end user devices, Johnny stepped up to the challenge. While balancing the regular tasks requested of his team to support caregivers during the implementation which included training, fielding questions, and keeping caregivers that were new to the software organized and on track to be prepared for the Go-Live Johnny also assisted my team. There were several tasks we requested of him and his team which included validation of hardware deployment and configuration and testing of all workstations. During the main event for testing Johnny and his team Johnny and his team did a great job working around patient care and caregivers as this was a production environment in an active hospital. His demeanor with peers and colleagues was exemplary and if we had an opening on our team, I am confident we would have gladly recruited him to work for us. His clinical experience and understanding of technology is very helpful when bridging the gap for customers.

fixedListComponent.text:
Over the past two year plus I have had the pleasure of working directly with Alvin Chung at Providence Health & Services. During the time we worked together my role was a Principal Project Manager and later a Senior Manager of a team that was heavily involved with the implementation of the Epic electronic medical record for Covenant Health in Texas and New Mexico. My direct reports interacted with Alvin daily and I served as an escalation point for the holistic project.

Alvin is professional, accountable, and possesses a passion for the details and customer satisfaction. In his role as an IS Project Manager he was responsible to attend and report out progress and barriers daily, communicate directly with the clinical caregivers when scheduling and entering their workspace. The clinical environment takes compassion and empathy; both of which Alvin displays. 

Other key skills would be his ability to develop relationships and trust with the key stakeholders and team members. This was accomplished by being accountable, knowledgeable, flexible, and approachable. Any organization would be lucky to have him.

section_components.caption: April 15, 2024, William (Al) was senior to Johnny but didn't manage Johnny directly
section_components.subtitle: Senior Leader Orchestrating Strategic Programs & Projects | Business Operations Expert | Change Management Champion | Driving Digital Transformation | Activating Strategies with Data Analytics & Lean Six Sigma

fixedListComponent.text: Working with Johnny during our Epic implementation was a pleasure. His professionalism and leadership skills shined bright and when we needed individuals to step up to lead groups for testing end user devices, Johnny stepped up to the challenge. While balancing the regular tasks requested of his team to support caregivers during the implementation which included training, fielding questions, and keeping caregivers that were new to the software organized and on track to be prepared for the Go-Live Johnny also assisted my team. There were several tasks we requested of him and his team which included validation of hardware deployment and configuration and testing of all workstations. During the main event for testing Johnny and his team Johnny and his team did a great job working around patient care and caregivers as this was a production environment in an active hospital. His demeanor with peers and colleagues was exemplary and if we had an opening on our team, I am confident we would have gladly recruited him to work for us. His clinical experience and understanding of technology is very helpful when bridging the gap for customers.

section_components.caption: August 17, 2022, William (Al) was senior to Alvin but didn't manage Alvin directly
section_components.subtitle: Principal Project Program Manager at UnitedHealth

fixedListComponent.text:
Over the past two year plus I have had the pleasure of working directly with Alvin Chung at Providence Health & Services. During the time we worked together my role was a Principal Project Manager and later a Senior Manager of a team that was heavily involved with the implementation of the Epic electronic medical record for Covenant Health in Texas and New Mexico. My direct reports interacted with Alvin daily and I served as an escalation point for the holistic project.

Alvin is professional, accountable, and possesses a passion for the details and customer satisfaction. In his role as an IS Project Manager he was responsible to attend and report out progress and barriers daily, communicate directly with the clinical caregivers when scheduling and entering their workspace. The clinical environment takes compassion and empathy; both of which Alvin displays. 

Other key skills would be his ability to develop relationships and trust with the key stakeholders and team members. This was accomplished by being accountable, knowledgeable, flexible, and approachable. Any organization would be lucky to have him.

description.text: Chosen for financial leadership of a 160-bed, $250M net revenue acute-care hospital. linkedin_data.name: Brian Veditz
linkedin_data.headline: IS Program Manager, Providence Health & Services
linkedin_data.summary: IS Program Manager with an extensive background in IS Infrastructure Projects.
linkedin_data.about: IS Program Manager with an extensive background in IS Infrastructure Projects.

description.text: Serving as IS Program Manager in the Mergers, Acquistions & Technology Enablement group working on multiple new Construction & Remodel Projects and Programs from small Clinic Acquisitions to large Hospital buildouts.  Projects encompassed the deployment of new Networking, Telecom and Desktop Equipment as well as migration from Paper or legacy EMR systems to EPIC in extremely constrained schedules.

Served as Program Manager for the Careconnect Command Center, Triage Desk & Call Center Projects, overseeing the implementation of a 300+ user, 150+ VoIP ACD Phone System to support the CareConnect Go-Live, the largest single-day, full-functionality Go-Live in Epic's history.

Managed the transition of end device systems infrastructure into the new Ronald Reagan UCLA Medical Center & Santa Monica UCLA Orthopaedic Hospital, ensuring smooth IT decommissioning of the Center of Health Sciences (CHS) Building.

Created and refined processes and procedures for the IT Project Management Office (ITPMO), facilitating effective project management and supporting team members.
Provided backup to the PMO Director, assisting with NPR meetings, training, and mentoring of team members.

Project Coordinator for Windows 2003 Server Migration at Southern California Edison. Supported large Data Center Server migration project by performing technical and business assessments on the installed Windows 2000 WinTel Server and application infrastructure as well as performing technical interviews with business owners, development and other project stakeholders. Created management reports, extracts and charts utilizing Access, Excel & VB Scripts. Developed Migration Flowcharts, Design Documents and Technical Procedures.

Led and prioritized the workload of 3 teams consisting of 12 project technicians and 3 team leads, ensuring successful completion of enterprise-wide projects including Y2K, Desktop Optimization, and Token Ring to Ethernet Conversion.

Conducted technical due diligence activities, assessing appropriate technologies, solution designs, and vendor selections.

Oversaw the hiring, training, and disbandment of the Ethernet Project team.

Provided comprehensive desktop, server, and network support to employees, ensuring compliance with company policies and procedures.

Designed and implemented a Microsoft Access Invoicing and Sales application for the company's Product Sales Division.

activities.text: 4 day course to prepare for PMP

While many courses in manufacturing focus on the mechanical operations and processes, this certificate focuses on maximizing the performance of the entire system. fixedListComponent.text: Darren has one of the strongest positive, motivational personalities I have ever encountered. Darren is a champion of strong morals and ethics, combined with customer service. As such, he was always promoting our team of managers to do the right thing. This training has given me the knowledge base on which I have built my career!

linkedin_data.headline: Divisional Compliance and Technology Director of Pharmacy at Providence Health & Services
linkedin_data.summary:
MISSION

To align my skills and talents with what is needed in the healthcare system to build effective and efficient systems that support optimized patient-centric results. 

WHAT HAS HELPED ME SUCCEED

Proven track record of high performance; employing strong organizational skills, leadership, efficiency, and thorough knowledge regarding many aspects of pharmacy processes and regulations to achieve organization goals: cost-savings, quality, labor efficiency, timely delivery, and safety.

WHERE I'VE MADE A DIFFERENCE

Improving the medication use process and unifying teams to drive organizational change are achievements throughout my career. 

A few select examples include:
● Exceeded formulation management and utilization savings goal each year.  Saved $441K in formulary management against a goal of $100K, and captured $3M in 340B savings.. 
● Oversight of design and remodel of a hospital central pharmacy, including longitudinal LEAN project focused on optimizing workflow efficiency and reducing waste. 
● Controlled Substance accountability operation and strategic planning for 8 hospitals that included design of medication use system and development of regulatory mock audit procedures.  

MY LEADERSHIP STYLE

I bring a collaborative leadership style that is focused and productive. I take pride in the assisting caregivers to utilize their skills and talents in ways that are meaningful to them and the organization.  A hospital CEO once said to me, "I appreciate that I never have to worry about pharmacy because I know you have it all handled."  

WHAT SETS ME APART

● Dedication
● Organization
● Integrity
● Compassion
● Work-ethic
● Technology expertise
● Transparency
